x4freetext: For short-lived fission products, 200 uL nitrate
solutions of 244Cm (0.55 mg/mL) sealed in different
polypropylene tube were covered with 1 mm thick cadmium
foils and doubly sealed in alkathene bags.
The targets were irradiated for 3-10 minutes using
pneumatic carrier facility of the heavy-water-moderated
natural uranium-fueled CIRUS reactor at a flux of
For long-lived fission products, 96 ug of
electrodeposited target of 244Cm (99.43 atom %) on
platinum planchet was covered with 75 um thick Lexan
foil.
It was then irradiated for 60 minutes in the highly
enriched uranium-fueled light-water-moderated
swimming pool reactor APSARA at a flux of
Two different HPGe detectors connected to two
separate PC-based 4096 channel analyzers were used
for the gamma-ray counting.
For short-lived fission products, 80 cc detector with
relative efficiency of 20% was used.
For long-lived fission products, a 120 cc with relative
efficiency of 30% was used.
The resolution of the detector systems were 2.0 keV and
1.8 keV full width at half maximum (FWHM) at 1332.5 keV
gamma-line of 60Co for the 80 cc and 120 cc detectors,
respectively.
counting statistics (1-10%)
overall systematic error
(4-6%) due to uncertainties in:
Irradiation time (0.1-0.8%)
detector efficiency calibration (~3%)
half-life of the fission products (~1%)
gamma-ray intensity (2-5%)
dead time of the detector system (<10%)
